<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,676,1135]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,444,748,775]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">General distribution</emphasis>
. Indo-West Pacific, ranging from the Arabian Gulf (
<collectingCountry box="[1021,1070,749,775]" name="Iran" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1081,1166,749,775]" name="Kuwait" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1176,1235,749,775]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">UAE</collectingCountry>
) to 
<collectingCountry box="[1277,1344,749,775]" name="Japan" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry name="Australia" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Australia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[234,407,785,811]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Osawa, M. &amp; Chan, T. Y." box="[422,661,785,811]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274" pagination="67 - 181" refId="ref16308" refString="Osawa, M. &amp; Chan, T. Y. (2010) Part III. Porcellanidae (porcelain crabs). In: Chan, T. Y. (Ed.), Crustacean fauna of Taiwan: crablike anomurans (Hippoidea, Lithodoidea and Porcellanidae). National Taiwan Ocean University, Keelung, pp. 67 - 181." type="book chapter" year="2010">Osawa &amp; Chan 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Naderloo, R. &amp; Turkay, M." box="[672,960,785,811]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274" pagination="1 - 67" refId="ref15707" refString="Naderloo, R. &amp; Turkay, M. (2012) Decapod crustaceans of the littoral and shallow sublittoral Iranian coast of the Persian Gulf: faunistics, biodiversity and zoogeography. Zootaxa, 3374 (1), 1 - 67. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3374.1.1" type="journal article" year="2012">Naderloo &amp; Türkay 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="274" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,676,1135]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,821,847]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Ecology</emphasis>
. Intertidal and subtidal, down to 
<quantity box="[667,727,820,847]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="274" unit="m" value="55.0">55 m</quantity>
; frequently in sponges (
<figureCitation box="[996,1095,820,847]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1435,181,1870]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 15. Polyonyx obesulus Miers, 1884: A—male from Failaka Island, Kuwait (MNHN-IU-2019-3186), dorsal view; B—same, with partly opened host sponge, frontodorsal view. Photographs by A. Anker." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3909107" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3909107/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Fig. 15B</figureCitation>
) and coral crevices, in the latter case presumably associated with cryptic sponges (
<bibRefCitation author="Osawa, M. &amp; Chan, T. Y." box="[751,993,857,883]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274" pagination="67 - 181" refId="ref16308" refString="Osawa, M. &amp; Chan, T. Y. (2010) Part III. Porcellanidae (porcelain crabs). In: Chan, T. Y. (Ed.), Crustacean fauna of Taiwan: crablike anomurans (Hippoidea, Lithodoidea and Porcellanidae). National Taiwan Ocean University, Keelung, pp. 67 - 181." type="book chapter" year="2010">Osawa &amp; Chan 2010</bibRefCitation>
); the single specimen from Failaka was found in the same yellow sponge as several individuals of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nobili" authorityYear="1904" box="[806,949,894,919]" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octoceras">
<emphasis box="[806,949,894,919]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">U. octoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="274" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,676,1135]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,929,955]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Remarks</emphasis>
. As pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation author="Osawa, M. &amp; Chan, T. Y." box="[525,779,929,955]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274" pagination="67 - 181" refId="ref16308" refString="Osawa, M. &amp; Chan, T. Y. (2010) Part III. Porcellanidae (porcelain crabs). In: Chan, T. Y. (Ed.), Crustacean fauna of Taiwan: crablike anomurans (Hippoidea, Lithodoidea and Porcellanidae). National Taiwan Ocean University, Keelung, pp. 67 - 181." type="book chapter" year="2010">Osawa &amp; Chan (2010)</bibRefCitation>
, the taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miers" authorityYear="1884" box="[979,1104,929,955]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Podocallichirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesulus">
<emphasis box="[979,1104,929,955]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">P. obesulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat problematic and a revision of the species is necessary. In this context, the taxonomic status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nobili" authorityYear="1906" box="[1003,1140,965,991]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Podocallichirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvidens">
<emphasis box="[1003,1140,965,991]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">P. parvidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, originally described from the Arabian Gulf (
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili, G." box="[353,504,1001,1027]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274" pagination="13 - 159" refId="ref16089" refString="Nobili, G. (1906 a) Mission J. Bonnier er Ch. Perez (Golfe Persique, 1901). Crustaces Decapodes et Stomatopodes. Bulletin Scientifique de La France et de La Belgique, 90, 13 - 159." type="journal article" year="1906">Nobili 1906a</bibRefCitation>
, b) and later synonimised with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miers" authorityYear="1884" box="[853,978,1001,1027]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Podocallichirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesulus">
<emphasis box="[853,978,1001,1027]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">P. obesulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, may need a reassessment. Nevertheless, the colour pattern of the Kuwaiti specimen corresponds fairly well to that of the Taiwanese specimen in 
<bibRefCitation author="Osawa, M. &amp; Chan, T. Y." pageId="23" pageNumber="274" pagination="67 - 181" refId="ref16308" refString="Osawa, M. &amp; Chan, T. Y. (2010) Part III. Porcellanidae (porcelain crabs). In: Chan, T. Y. (Ed.), Crustacean fauna of Taiwan: crablike anomurans (Hippoidea, Lithodoidea and Porcellanidae). National Taiwan Ocean University, Keelung, pp. 67 - 181." type="book chapter" year="2010">Osawa &amp; Chan (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. The species seems to be relatively common in the Arabian Gulf, but is herein recorded for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[269,355,1109,1135]" name="Kuwait" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
